place.name: LITTLE WELNETHAM
place.gazetteerText: WELNETHAM (Little), a parish in Thingoe district, Suffolk; 1 mile NNE of W. r. station, and 3¾ SE of Bury-St. Edmunds. Post town, Bury-St. Edmunds. Acres, 592. Real property, £1,086. Pop., 194. Houses, 41. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Ely. Value, £155. Patron, the Marquis of Bristol. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
